1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,044
[ Mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,169 --> 00:00:03,504
[ Penguins chirp ]

3
00:00:05,047 --> 00:00:06,882
[ All cheering ]

4
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,095
[ Screeches ]

5
00:00:12,888 --> 00:00:13,972
s Adventure time J

6
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,390
J Come on, grab your friends &

7
00:00:15,474 --> 00:00:18,060
J We'll go
to very distant lands ;&

8
00:00:18,143 --> 00:00:20,395
s With Cake the cat
and Fionna the human 7

9
00:00:20,479 --> 00:00:22,147
s The fun will never end J

10
00:00:22,231 --> 00:00:24,274
J It's adventure time &

11
00:00:28,195 --> 00:00:32,783
;7

12
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:36,787
These ghoul dudes
take the form

13
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,664
of whatever
you're thinking about.

14
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,210
[ Chainsaws buzz ]

15
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:46,797
An angry --
no, shy shark baby.

16
00:00:51,802 --> 00:00:55,305
What if life was always just
constant fun times on the river?

17
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:57,933
Let's never do
anything boring ever again.

18
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:01,353
Yes, let's never do anything
boring ever ag--

19
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:02,479
[ Beeping ]

20
00:01:02,563 --> 00:01:04,606
Time for Ice King's
boring book reading.

21
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,733
Aw, come on!

22
00:01:06,817 --> 00:01:08,318
He's just gonna read
those weird stories

23
00:01:08,402 --> 00:01:10,112
that are basically
about us.

24
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:12,614
I kind of dig getting
loosely adapted.

25
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:17,578
Ice King: Fionna spoke with the
voice of an angelic choir.

26
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:20,706
"You can have the rest of the
screaming chili cheese dip

27
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:21,957
if you want," she said.

28
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:24,751
[ Sniffles ]
"It's totally fine."

29
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:26,295
The end.

30
00:01:27,713 --> 00:01:29,548
I said "the end"!

31
00:01:30,007 --> 00:01:31,258
[ Applause ]

32
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:32,509
[ Chair squeaks ]

33
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:34,177
Let's get
some questions.

34
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,805
Where do
your ideas come from?

35
00:01:37,264 --> 00:01:39,141
They're beamed
into my melon at night --

36
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:41,476
same as everybody else.
Next!

37
00:01:41,852 --> 00:01:44,646
Woman: I have more of
a criticism than a question.

38
00:01:44,730 --> 00:01:47,024
I am very open
to criticism!

39
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:49,860
Your story was
completely wrong.

40
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:51,570
And how would you know?

41
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:53,405
I know...

42
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:55,198
because I am...

43
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:57,326
[ Stick clacks ]
Fionna!

44
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,077
All: [ Gasps ]

45
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:01,830
I can show you
what really happened.

46
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:04,082
It's all on this tape!

47
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:06,668
All: Ooh!
Jake: What format
is that?

48
00:02:06,752 --> 00:02:07,628
[ VCR clicks, whirs ]

49
00:02:09,588 --> 00:02:12,132
According to this map,
we're very close.

50
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:14,134
-Hey. Hey.
- Hi. Hey.

51
00:02:14,718 --> 00:02:15,927
There's the door.

52
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:22,351
[ Door knob rattles ]
Aw, it's locked.

53
00:02:22,601 --> 00:02:23,769
I'll getusin

54
00:02:23,935 --> 00:02:26,605
with key... eye!

55
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:30,025
Bam!

56
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:33,612
"Eye" got it.
You get it, Fionna?

57
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:36,531
Yeah, but it's a stretch.

58
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,533
[ Laughter ]

59
00:02:38,617 --> 00:02:40,285
There I am.

60
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:42,371
[ Door creaks ]
Fionna: [ Sighs ]

61
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:45,374
Next time we find a map
lying in the backyard,

62
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:46,792
we should think twice.

63
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,835
Cake: At least we get
this fancy coffin.

64
00:02:50,796 --> 00:02:52,047
How's it look?

65
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,383
It's a decent addition
to the treasure vestibule

66
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:56,635
but still kind of
a letdown.

67
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,553
You know what's
never a letdown?

68
00:02:59,221 --> 00:03:01,515
Cookie sauce
review party.

69
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:03,892
Yeah!
Cookie dip.

70
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:06,645
Screaming chili cheese
versus sriracha ranch.

71
00:03:07,354 --> 00:03:08,480
[ Lid creaks ]

72
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:09,940
[ VCR clicks, whirs ]

73
00:03:11,942 --> 00:03:14,194
[ Light switch clicks ]
Was it real?
Who was filming all that?

74
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:15,821
Wenk, wenk.
Needs more hunks!

75
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:19,574
Dude, I literally have
one bazillion questions.

76
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:21,993
Uh, excuse me,
Miss Fionna...

77
00:03:22,077 --> 00:03:23,453
where did this video
come fr-o-o-om!

78
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:24,830
Fionna!

79
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:28,542
I always knew we'd meet one day
and become best friends.

80
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:32,546
So, uh, remember that time when
Cake caught Ruse Goose,

81
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:34,589
the notorious goose
pickpocket?

82
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:37,342
That was
such a long time ago.

83
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:39,845
But during trial,
you realized she was framed

84
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:42,514
'cause it was actually
Abracadanielle pretending

85
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:43,932
to be a goose
all along!

86
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:44,975
[ Hisses ]

87
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:46,852
Can I also ask
a question?

88
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:47,894
Besties only.

89
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,355
I was just gonna ask if we could
see more of the tape.

90
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,982
Oh, yeah, can we?

91
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:53,734
I don't think so.

92
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:57,195
All right,
just a little more.

93
00:03:58,029 --> 00:03:59,406
[ VCR clicks, whirs ]

94
00:04:00,449 --> 00:04:02,242
[ Lid creaks ]

95
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:06,037
[ Yawns ]

96
00:04:09,124 --> 00:04:11,752
Oh... my... glob.

97
00:04:12,335 --> 00:04:13,587
It's a mummy!

98
00:04:14,129 --> 00:04:16,506
That's right.
I'ma mummy!

99
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,383
Aww,
Yeah, you are.

100
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:20,093
And a real cutie, too.

101
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:23,054
I'm not cute!
I'm horrible!

102
00:04:23,138 --> 00:04:24,890
[ Groans menacingly ]

103
00:04:25,015 --> 00:04:26,183
Want to hang?

104
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,100
[ VCR clicks, static crackles ]

105
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:28,769
Okay, that's enough.

106
00:04:28,852 --> 00:04:30,145
Both: Aw!

107
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:31,938
I want to see more.

108
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:34,691
I don't want to wear it out.
It's my only copy.

109
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:36,526
And it's
very important to me.

110
00:04:37,194 --> 00:04:39,237
Library closes in five.

111
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:40,781
Click, click, click.
[ Light switch clicks ]

112
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:43,575
So, where you heading now?

113
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:47,162
Guess I'll go back to the dump
under the bridge where I live.

114
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,414
I'd invite you over,
but I don't have a sofa

115
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:50,665
or TV or anything.

116
00:04:50,749 --> 00:04:51,958
It's literally a dump.

117
00:04:52,042 --> 00:04:54,920
I have a TW.
My crib is equipped.

118
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,838
Oh, really?

119
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:58,965
Hey, you should move in!

120
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:01,134
Please live
with me, Fionna.

121
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,888
This is the sweet spot.

122
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:08,099
My roo-- Oh!
I wasn't expecting guests.

123
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:11,144
[Chuckles] Not that you mind
a bit of dirt, right?

124
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,271
Nice, huh?

125
00:05:13,355 --> 00:05:15,273
So, this is my room now.

126
00:05:15,357 --> 00:05:16,942
Only the best for Fionna.

127
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,903
Ice King: Oh, yeah.
I like this room, too.

128
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:22,447
It's where I do
all my deep thinking.

129
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:27,869
Man, I still can't believe it --
the Fionna in my bathroom,

130
00:05:27,953 --> 00:05:29,621
touching my toothbrush,

131
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:32,123
throwing it
into my little trash can.

132
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,292
Fionna taking charge!

133
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:36,086
That's what heroes do.

134
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:38,296
You're a so much better hero
than Finn.

135
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:39,297
I know.

136
00:05:39,381 --> 00:05:41,007
Plus, don't tell Jake,

137
00:05:41,091 --> 00:05:43,385
but I've always been more
of a cat person.

138
00:05:44,261 --> 00:05:46,596
Where is Cake the Cat?
Cake?

139
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:48,265
Cake?

140
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:49,558
Cake is gone.

141
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:52,102
Some years back, there was
an adventure mishap.

142
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:54,354
I don't feel comfortable
talking about it.

143
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:56,439
Oh, okay.

144
00:05:57,190 --> 00:06:00,151
Hey, you still haven't
shown me where you keep

145
00:06:00,235 --> 00:06:02,279
your Fionna-and-Cake
tapes.

146
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:04,781
Sorry, no can do.
What?

147
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:06,116
Don't you have tapes?

148
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:09,911
Oh, yeah, I got loads of tapes,
but they're super private.

149
00:06:10,245 --> 00:06:11,538
Maybe you'll change
your mind

150
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:14,165
once you see more
of my mummy adventure?

151
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:16,543
Yay!
I'll get snacks.

152
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:18,044
[ Static crackles ]

153
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:22,215
[ Laughter ]

154
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:23,592
[ Groans ]

155
00:06:23,675 --> 00:06:25,176
Hey, what's wrong?

156
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:28,930
I have... a curse!

157
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:30,515
Oh, no.
Oh, no.

158
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:32,726
How can we save you,
tiny mummy?

159
00:06:32,934 --> 00:06:35,353
The curse can only be broken
by strong black coffee

160
00:06:35,437 --> 00:06:37,314
and fancy muffins
from Breakfast Kingdom.

161
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:38,857
I know that place.

162
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:41,109
It has a really long line
on weekends.

163
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:43,403
Yes!
That sounds like the one.

164
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:45,989
Be a hero and fetch unto me
the sacred breakfast.

165
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:47,532
Don't you worry,
little guy.

166
00:06:47,616 --> 00:06:50,201
We'll save you!

167
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:54,205
[ Laughs ]

168
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:57,626
[ VCR clicks, static crackles ]

169
00:06:57,834 --> 00:06:59,377
Okay, that's the end
of the tape.

170
00:06:59,628 --> 00:07:00,503
Really?

171
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:02,631
My stories usually get
wrapped up neater.

172
00:07:02,714 --> 00:07:05,091
[ Chuckles ]
Wrapped up -- mummies.

173
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:07,594
Yeah, well,
there's no more, so...

174
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:09,930
You wouldn't know this,

175
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:12,474
but old heroes need
a lot of sleep.

176
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:14,809
I did know that.

177
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:16,895
See you in the morning.
[ Tape clicks ]

178
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:19,439
[ Click echoing,
ominous tone plays ]

179
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:21,274
Okay.

180
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:25,904
Fionna?
You awake?

181
00:07:26,196 --> 00:07:27,989
I made you
a midnight snack.

182
00:07:28,073 --> 00:07:30,200
[ Snoring ]

183
00:07:33,036 --> 00:07:35,497
[ Munching ]

184
00:07:37,415 --> 00:07:39,501
[ Sighs, snores ]

185
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,712
[ VCR clicks, static crackles ]

186
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:44,506
Mummy, we're home.

187
00:07:44,631 --> 00:07:46,466
[ Gasps ]
I knew it.

188
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:47,926
Where did it go?

189
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:51,304
Maybe it had to go back into
its coffin Dracula-style.

190
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:52,764
Mummy?

191
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:54,557
We got your breakfast.

192
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:56,226
Hmm.

193
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,852
[ Coins rattling ]
Shh! What's that?

194
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:01,147
Nyeh.

195
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:03,024
That's our treasure!

196
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:06,361
Stay away.
You'll get cursed.

197
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:08,196
[ Groans menacingly ]

198
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:11,282
I take the curse off of me
and put it back on you.

199
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:14,285
You understand nothing
of mummy curses!

200
00:08:14,369 --> 00:08:15,578
Our treasure!

201
00:08:16,538 --> 00:08:17,747
Our muffins!

202
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:25,547
Uhh... do not look
upon a naked mummy.

203
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:26,798
It's bad luck.

204
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:28,675
Both: Queen of O007?!

205
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:29,926
That's right.

206
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,429
I snuck in here to pretend
to steal your stash

207
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:34,139
and teach you
a valuable lesson.

208
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:37,183
Never invite strangers
into your home,

209
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,227
no matter how cool
they seem and are.

210
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:41,312
You should be
thanking me really.

211
00:08:41,396 --> 00:08:43,231
[ VCR clicks, whirs ]

212
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:45,108
Of course.

213
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:47,694
She didn't want me
to see the end of the tape

214
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,863
because she's not Fionna.

215
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:52,449
She's... a mummy!

216
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:54,367
Aah!

217
00:08:57,245 --> 00:08:59,164
[ Ominous music plays ]

218
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:01,708
[ Whimpering ]

219
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:04,711
Other Fionna: Come on.

220
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:07,422
They're all just him?

221
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:08,923
Imposter!

222
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:10,592
Reveal yourself!

223
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,677
Aah! [Gasps]
Knock it off!

224
00:09:12,761 --> 00:09:14,262
You're the knock-off!

225
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:16,890
What?
You're not Fionna!

226
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:19,934
How did you --
Show me your true form!

227
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,522
Aha! Huh?

228
00:09:24,606 --> 00:09:26,858
What kind of mummy
are you supposed to be?

229
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:29,360
No kind!
I'm just an old lady.

230
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:32,030
Who likes to dress up
as Fionna?

231
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:34,949
It makes me feel
confident, okay?

232
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,077
Plus, I look really good
in this outfit.

233
00:09:38,703 --> 00:09:41,164
Look, I used to be
very shy...

234
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,000
tinkering with my tech
stuff all night,

235
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:45,794
sleeping all day.

236
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:49,380
But one evening, I intercepted
a strange signal.

237
00:09:49,464 --> 00:09:51,174
I was mesmerized.

238
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:54,010
I watched that tape
like 100 times

239
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:57,639
before I finally stepped
out of my cave a hew woman,

240
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:00,475
determined to find
more Fionna and Cake.

241
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:03,728
I roamed Ooo for years
with no luck.

242
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:06,773
But then, I found out
about you,

243
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:09,776
and I hatched a plan
to steal your tapes.

244
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:11,027
What?

245
00:10:11,111 --> 00:10:13,279
I don't have
any Fionna and Cake tapes.

246
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:14,781
I know!

247
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:18,034
All of your tapes are filled
with embarrassing diaries.

248
00:10:18,409 --> 00:10:20,912
If I met them,
I'd definitely record it.

249
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:23,998
Fionna and Cake
aren't real, you ding-dong!

250
00:10:24,082 --> 00:10:26,751
They're just, like, a TV show
from the past or something.

251
00:10:26,835 --> 00:10:28,962
You're the ding-dong, lady!

252
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,631
You tricked an old,
defenseless Ice King.

253
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:34,134
[ Crying ]

254
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:36,636
Look, I didn't mean
to hurt you.

255
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:38,263
You lied to me.

256
00:10:38,346 --> 00:10:40,557
Fionna would never lie --
never.

257
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:44,060
Oh, glob, you're right.
I'm not like Fionna.

258
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:45,770
I'm the mummy!

259
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:48,690
[ Wailing ]
[ Crying ]

260
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,150
Wenk.
Huh?

261
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,901
Well, that was
